name: market for navy bean | navy bean | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/27443/documentation

This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for 'navy bean', in the Global geography.;The dataset considers transportation from the producer to the consumer of this product, transportation distances are based on default transport distances for markets (found in file 'Default Transport Assumptions' at https://www.ecoinvent.org/support/documents-and-files/documents-and-files.html).

This activity starts at the gate of the activities that produce 'navy bean',  within the geography of Global.

This activity ends with the supply of  'navy bean', to the consumers of this product. Transport is included. Product losses during transportation are assumed negligible and are therefore not included.
